=\"row\">Alias</th><td>\nThe Lace Serpent<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Title</th><td>\nLady of <a href=\"/index.php/Duskendale\" title=\"Duskendale\">Duskendale</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiance</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/House_Darklyn\" title=\"House Darklyn\">House Darklyn</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Myr\" title=\"Myr\">Myrish</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Myr\" title=\"Myr\">Myr</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Died</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_277_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">277&#160;AC</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><br /><a href=\"/index.php/Duskendale\" title=\"Duskendale\">Duskendale</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Spouse</th><td>\nLord <a href=\"/index.php/Denys_Darklyn\" title=\"Denys Darklyn\">Denys Darklyn</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Books</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i> (mentioned)</li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>Lady <b>Serala of Myr</b>, known as <b>the Lace Serpent</b>, was the wife of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Denys_Darklyn\" title=\"Denys Darklyn\">Denys Darklyn</a>, the last <a href=\"/index.php/House_Darklyn\" title=\"House Darklyn\">Darklyn</a> lord of <a href=\"/index.php/Duskendale\" title=\"Duskendale\">Duskendale</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Serala_of_Myr&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Smallfolk\" title=\"Smallfolk\">smallfolk</a> blame Serala for the fall of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Darklyn\" title=\"House Darklyn\">House Darklyn</a>, claiming she put the seed of rebellion in her husband's ear with <a href=\"/index.php/Myr\" title=\"Myr\">Myrish</a> poison, leading to the <a href=\"/index.php/Defiance_of_Duskendale\" title=\"Defiance of Duskendale\">Defiance of Duskendale</a>. Her actual role in the matter is not truly known, but from that belief held by the populace came her name, <i>the Lace <a href=\"/index.php/Serpent\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Serpent\">Serpent</a></i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>During the Defiance, her husband, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Denys_Darklyn\" title=\"Denys Darklyn\">Denys Darklyn</a>, made the mistake of holding captive King <a href=\"/index.php/Aerys_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Aerys II Targaryen\">Aerys II Targaryen</a>. Following his liberation and the end of the Defiance, Aerys went on a killing rampage. Serala's husband and all of his house were beheaded, while she was burned alive, though her tongue was torn out first, along with her female parts, with which it was said she enslaved her lordly husband. Half of <a href=\"/index.php/Duskendale\" title=\"Duskendale\">Duskendale</a> stated that Aerys was still too kind to her, believing the Defiance would have never happened had Lord Denys married a <a href=\"/index.php/House_Stokeworth\" title=\"House Stokeworth\">Stokeworth</a> or a <a href=\"/index.php/House_Staunton\" title=\"House Staunton\">Staunton</a> instead.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf_the_targaryen_kings:_aerys_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf_the_targaryen_kings:_aerys_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Family\">Family</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Serala_of_Myr&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Family\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div style=\"overflow:auto;\"><table cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" border=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:separate;font: 90% sans-serif;\">\n<tbody><tr align=\"center\"><td r